text.tspan: Top of block. R and L is for whether
the tile is on the left or right side of the
combination of blocks(could also swap L
and L.) R and L is used for rest of tiles
Location is encoded with a numbers of bits.
These bits are made of an A tile, B tile, and
a C tile. The way the A, B, C tiles are combined
to form a bit is to the right.
Value is encoded with the value and whether it is on the left or right of
F tiles are used to have right side of the block in the correct
position as well as transfer information from the
right side to the left side for input candidate and endstate.
Bottom of block. BL changes state to either connect
on side for when connecting with other blocks or on
bottom for when checking if input candidate.
Encodes whether input candidate or not
